The paper focuses on developing a decentralized framework for solving the distributed machine learning problem, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses communication efficiency and network topology, which are relevant to distributed computing (cs.DC) and distributed systems (cs.DS). The privacy-aware aspect of the proposed algorithm suggests that it may also be relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and systems and control (cs.SY) sub-categories.
